The PDP presidential candidate Atiku Abubakar has yet to cast his vote at his polling unit of Ajiya in Yola North Local Government Area of Adamawa whereas the APC flagbearer and President Muhammadu Buhari voted minutes after polling started on Saturday.
This is almost one hour after the commencement of the Presidential and National Assembly elections nationwide.
Some of Atiku’s aides who arrived at the unit, however, said the PDP flag-bearer “`should be coming any moment from now”.
President Muhammadu Buhari, the APC candidate, voted four minutes after the commencement of polling in Daura, Katsina State.
While voting, Buhari commended Nigerians for conducting themselves peacefully during as voting began across the nation.
